@startuml
actor "User Agent" as UA
participant "Content removal API\n<<interface>>\n()" as CRAPI
control "User Manager\n<<boundary>>\n-->" as UM
database "User database" as UD
database "Content database" as CD

note right of User Agent : Should also include a CSRF token to prevent admins who are also visit other, potentially XSS vulnerable or malicious sites from helping an unkown actor remove content without authorization.


UA ->> CRAPI: Removal request (HTTP POST), contains ID of content to be removed.\r\ralt [Request is deemed valid] \ralternate alt [Failed to validate removal request]\rReturn HTTP status code 403 Forbidden to signal reason for failure.\rend alternate end 
CRAPI->UM: Retrieve role of requesting user_
activate UM
UM-->UD: Fetch user information from database_\nreturn query result._
deactivate UM
UM --> CRAPI: Return user role_.
crapi-> crapi: Validate removal request__
group Request validation failed
    note over ua,capi: return http error message indicating why the reqest was rejected.__
end group
else if(User has admin role) then
   activate um  
     loop while(content exists in db){ fetch next chunk; process chunks until done;} deactivateum else{ send back response saying there's nothing leftto delete} endifendifif(user not authorized )then retunhttpstatuscodeforbiddenelsesuccessfullyremovedcontentfromdbandreturnsuccesstouserafterthatwehavetwooptionsoneistoreturnanerrormessageindicatingwhytheremovalfailedorthesecondoptionwouldbetosimplysayokwithoutanyadditionalinformationdependingonwhatkindofsystemthisispartofi.e.' aspiration goal objective aim target destination endpoint outcome effect impact result output yield gain loss cost price value worth merit quality quantity size amount number degree level rank order priority importance significance meaning relevance relationship association linkage bond tie attachment commitment dedication devotion loyalty trust faith confidence certainty security safety risk danger threat vulnerability weakness strength power force energy effort action behavior conduct performance execution implementation delivery service work job task project assignment responsibility obligation duty rights holder claim ownership possession control dominion sway influence authority jurisdiction legitimacy credibility authenticity veracity accuracy truth fact fiction myth legend folk tale dream nightmare sleep wake dreaming hallucinating deluding illusional miraging phantasm spectering apparitional ghostliness spiritual entity being creature organism life form biological chemical physical elemental substance subjects matter materials things objects items artifacts products goods commodities assets properties wealth riches spoils booty treasures hoards caches accumulates collections assemblies aggregates clusters batches sets suites packages bundles kits toolboxes chests trunks boxes containers holders carriers transports vehicles crafts ships boats planes automobiles trucks trains buses cycles pedalcycles wheelchairs crutches sticks staves poles bars rods shafts beams girders columns pillars po